WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:04.091
[ Toto's "Rosanna" playing ]

00:04.091 --> 00:06.180
[ Off-key ] ♪ All I wanna do
when I wake up in the morning ♪

00:06.180 --> 00:09.096
♪ Is see your eyes ♪

00:09.096 --> 00:12.229
♪ Rosanna, Rosanna ♪

00:12.229 --> 00:14.318
♪ I never thought that
a girl like you ♪

00:14.318 --> 00:17.321
♪ Could ever care for me ♪

00:17.321 --> 00:20.498
♪ Rosanna ♪

00:20.498 --> 00:21.978
[ Laughs ]

00:23.719 --> 00:25.634
[ Falsetto voice ]
♪ All I wanna do ♪

00:25.634 --> 00:28.419
♪ In the middle of the night
is hold you tight ♪

00:28.419 --> 00:31.857
♪ Rosanna, Rosanna ♪

00:31.857 --> 00:38.342
♪ I didn't know you were looking
for more than I could ever be ♪

00:38.342 --> 00:42.825
♪ Not quite a year
since she went away ♪

00:42.825 --> 00:45.132
♪ Rosanna, yeah ♪

00:45.132 --> 00:47.482
Gentlemen.

00:47.482 --> 00:49.788
You're in the wrong place,
Inspector.

00:49.788 --> 00:51.355
Take-out's downstairs.

00:51.355 --> 00:53.705
[ Chuckles ] We're looking
for Sam Rydell.

00:53.705 --> 00:55.316
Never heard of him.

00:55.316 --> 00:58.275
Then you don't watch TV.

00:58.275 --> 01:00.234
[ Clears throat ]
Our records say that he called

01:00.234 --> 01:02.149
this club about 20 times
in the past 2 weeks.

01:02.149 --> 01:03.454
Maybe he's ordering egg rolls.

01:03.454 --> 01:05.326
You know,
if you write a Yelp review,

01:05.326 --> 01:07.458
you get 10% off
your next delivery.[ Man chuckles ]

01:07.458 --> 01:09.895
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:09.895 --> 01:11.810
That's cute. Give it to him.

01:11.810 --> 01:14.291
What's this?Open it.

01:14.291 --> 01:16.989
These are all current cases
that name the Tongs --

01:16.989 --> 01:19.427
prostitution, racketeering.

01:19.427 --> 01:21.429
We can handle this here
or down in Homicide.

01:21.429 --> 01:23.474
It's on you.

01:23.474 --> 01:24.910
♪♪

01:24.910 --> 01:27.522
[ Sighs ] I saw Sam
a few days ago.

01:27.522 --> 01:29.611
Yeah, we know. You roughed him
up pretty good.

01:29.611 --> 01:31.265
We had a conversation.Where'd he go?

01:31.265 --> 01:33.180
Well, if he's smart,
halfway to Mexico by now.

01:33.180 --> 01:35.486
Why is that?'Cause sandwich man owes us
some serious greens.

01:35.486 --> 01:37.053
So you threw him over
the bridge,

01:37.053 --> 01:38.794
wanted to teach him a lesson?I didn't do shit.

01:38.794 --> 01:40.448
If you want any more info,
you gotta talk to my lawyer.

01:40.448 --> 01:41.753
He's that drunk fool over there

01:41.753 --> 01:43.146
singing them
silly white man songs.

01:43.146 --> 01:45.235
All right, get up.
We're taking you in.

01:45.235 --> 01:47.759
[ Sniffs ]

01:47.759 --> 01:49.457
[ Table bangs on floor ]Come on, man!

01:49.457 --> 01:50.893
What's wrong with you?

01:50.893 --> 01:52.590
Chan: Inspectors.

01:54.070 --> 01:55.767
A word, please.

01:55.767 --> 01:57.726
[ Bottles clink ]

01:57.726 --> 01:59.815
[ Speaking Chinese ]

01:59.815 --> 02:01.730
[ Speaks Chinese ]

02:01.730 --> 02:04.515
I was just about to have
a little late night snack.

02:04.515 --> 02:06.256
Care to join me?

02:10.782 --> 02:13.089
[ Sighs ]

02:16.875 --> 02:19.226
[ Clears throat ]Egg roll?

02:19.226 --> 02:21.619
No, we're good.

02:21.619 --> 02:23.621
My grandmother's recipe.

02:23.621 --> 02:27.756
When I was a boy, I watched her
roll a hundred in one hour.

02:27.756 --> 02:31.499
She had the smallest fingers.
Good for delicate things.

02:31.499 --> 02:33.153
[ Chuckles ] I'm sorry.

02:33.153 --> 02:36.721
But you're not interested
in my, uh, culinary history.

02:36.721 --> 02:38.636
So how may I assist you?

02:38.636 --> 02:40.116
Sam Rydell.

02:40.116 --> 02:43.250
[ Speaking Chinese ]

02:43.250 --> 02:47.254
We found his car abandoned
on the Richmond Bridge.

02:47.254 --> 02:50.431
Your business card was tucked in
his jacket inside pocket.

02:50.431 --> 02:51.997
[ Glass clatters ]

02:56.698 --> 03:00.267
There are times when a client
does not repay his loan

03:00.267 --> 03:01.790
in a timely manner.

03:01.790 --> 03:06.098
I find fear motivates them
to do the right thing.

03:06.098 --> 03:07.622
Yeah, well, you scared him,
all right.

03:07.622 --> 03:09.014
He thought you were
gonna kill him.

03:09.014 --> 03:10.538
No.

03:10.538 --> 03:14.629
Fear is one thing,
but death is another.

03:14.629 --> 03:17.109
I did not build
such a successful business

03:17.109 --> 03:18.894
by burning money.

03:18.894 --> 03:22.854
Mr. Rydell is a feiyang,
cash cow.

03:22.854 --> 03:26.728
My people were farmers
from Guangzhou.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.947
And every good farmer knows

03:28.947 --> 03:31.863
one does not slaughter
a feiyang.

03:31.863 --> 03:35.215
One milks it.

03:35.215 --> 03:38.783
Mm-hmm.I would be sorry to lose
Mr. Rydell.

03:43.788 --> 03:45.268
[ Cheering ]

03:45.268 --> 03:48.619
Let's go. Come on.

03:48.619 --> 03:50.186
Damn!

03:50.186 --> 03:53.233
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:54.930 --> 03:56.975
[ Exhales deeply ]

03:56.975 --> 03:59.326
All right. [ Sighs ]

03:59.326 --> 04:00.805
Deal me in.

04:05.288 --> 04:06.681
A split.

04:06.681 --> 04:09.553
Okay, come on, God.

04:09.553 --> 04:11.425
Just be good to me one time.

04:12.817 --> 04:15.690
Come on. One time.

04:15.690 --> 04:18.736
Come on. Come on. Come on.

04:20.085 --> 04:22.523
Yes!

04:22.523 --> 04:24.438
Okay, all right.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.745
[ Exhales deeply ]

04:29.181 --> 04:32.402
[ Heart beating,
clock ticking ]

04:47.374 --> 04:48.984
[ Whispers indistinctly ]Please.

04:48.984 --> 04:50.899
Please, please. Yes!

04:50.899 --> 04:53.118
Thank you, Lord.Man: Yeah!

04:53.118 --> 04:56.339
Okay, come on, bust,
you rat bastard.

04:56.339 --> 04:58.080
No offense.

04:58.950 --> 05:00.430
Come on.

05:00.430 --> 05:01.953
Bust. Bust. Come on.

05:01.953 --> 05:04.565
[ Whispers ] Bust.

05:04.565 --> 05:08.351
♪♪

05:11.223 --> 05:12.790
Yes! [ Laughs ]

05:12.790 --> 05:15.053
[ Cheering ]Yes, I knew you could do it!

05:15.053 --> 05:18.187
The boy is back!
Don't bury me yet!

05:18.187 --> 05:20.232
[ Laughing ]

05:20.232 --> 05:23.279
Whoo! Okay.

05:23.279 --> 05:26.238
We are on a roll!

05:37.511 --> 05:40.514
♪♪

05:49.523 --> 05:52.874
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:52.874 --> 05:54.658
Hey.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.747
Right on time.Hey, good morning.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.183
Got you the daily special.

05:58.183 --> 06:00.534
Thanks.Yeah. Wanna...

06:00.534 --> 06:01.926
Yeah.

06:04.494 --> 06:07.410
So what'd you wanna tell me
you couldn't say over the phone?

06:07.410 --> 06:09.891
Well, I've been, uh,
been working for a bit

06:09.891 --> 06:12.372
on an investigative piece
about violence in the NFL

06:12.372 --> 06:14.025
off the field.

06:14.025 --> 06:17.899
And I wanted to share a tip
from an inside source

06:17.899 --> 06:20.510
about a player who pulled a gun
on Normandy.

06:20.510 --> 06:23.905
Okay, is this credible
or just more gossip?

06:23.905 --> 06:26.690
Well, Billy James is my source,
so yeah, it's credible.

06:26.690 --> 06:28.736
I think it's what
got him killed.

06:28.736 --> 06:32.827
Did he tell you
the player's name?

06:32.827 --> 06:35.482
Luke Wedman, former running back
for the Wildcats.

06:35.482 --> 06:36.831
Navarro:
Yeah, guy's a local hero.

06:36.831 --> 06:38.180
Scored the winning touchdown
for USC

06:38.180 --> 06:40.225
in the Rose Bowl senior year.

06:40.225 --> 06:42.532
Yeah, well, this hero pointed
a gun at Normandy Parker

06:42.532 --> 06:44.099
in the Wildcats' locker room.Why?

06:44.099 --> 06:46.014
Last game of the season,
Normandy was supposed

06:46.014 --> 06:48.146
to hand the ball off to Luke
for a gimme touchdown,

06:48.146 --> 06:50.758
but instead called an audible
and ran it in himself.

06:50.758 --> 06:52.760
Luke never scored
his 10th touchdown,

06:52.760 --> 06:55.023
which would've triggered
a $2 million performance bonus

06:55.023 --> 06:56.764
in his contract.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.940
How did the team keep it quiet?[ Telephone rings ]

06:58.940 --> 07:01.116
Lieutenant Koto.

07:01.116 --> 07:03.466
The pro football player pulls
a gun on the star quarterback,

07:03.466 --> 07:05.120
and nobody hears anything
about it?

07:05.120 --> 07:06.774
Not on Twitter, Facebook,
nothing?

07:06.774 --> 07:08.253
Who does Luke play for now?He doesn't.

07:08.253 --> 07:09.646
Guy rushed for 1,200 yards
that season,

07:09.646 --> 07:11.126
and he's still a free agent.

07:11.126 --> 07:13.998
Maybe Normandy Parker
leaked it to management.

07:13.998 --> 07:16.218
Luke could've blamed him
for ruining his career.

07:16.218 --> 07:19.047
Two in the head
and they're even.Okay, Billy James' murder.

07:19.047 --> 07:21.441
What's -- what's the connection?Maybe there is none.

07:21.441 --> 07:22.964
Thank you.

07:22.964 --> 07:25.880
Sam Rydell has been found.
That was Reno P.D.

07:25.880 --> 07:28.143
He had a heart attack last night
in a casino.

07:28.143 --> 07:29.666
Is he dead?

07:29.666 --> 07:31.233
No, they stented him.
He's stable.

07:31.233 --> 07:32.843
How come it took so long
for them to call us?

07:32.843 --> 07:34.497
There's an APB out.
Sam's all over the news.

07:34.497 --> 07:36.586
Yeah, he had a fake ID on him --
a couple, actually --

07:36.586 --> 07:38.153
and a Canadian passport.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.981
Wasn't until the day nurse
recognized him

07:39.981 --> 07:42.200
from his commercials that
she thought to call the cops.

07:42.200 --> 07:43.898
It seems he's ready to talk.

07:43.898 --> 07:46.640
Why don't you guys fly up there
and bring him back?

07:46.640 --> 07:49.251
He's at Reno General.Okay.

07:49.251 --> 07:51.340
The two of you
go interview Luke.

07:51.340 --> 07:53.690
My information is that
he spends most every day

07:53.690 --> 07:55.823
at Metro Fitness working out.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.433
Yeah, well,
old habits never die.

07:57.433 --> 07:58.869
Yeah.

08:06.137 --> 08:07.487
[ Clank ]

08:07.487 --> 08:08.966
[ Exhales ]

08:08.966 --> 08:10.533
[ Weights clank ]

08:12.666 --> 08:13.928
[ Sighs ]

08:17.322 --> 08:19.107
Luke Wedman?

08:19.107 --> 08:23.981
Terry English, SFPD, Homicide.
This is Inspector Mulligan.

08:23.981 --> 08:25.766
Why are you here?

08:25.766 --> 08:28.725
You're looking good, man.
I see you putting in the hours.

08:28.725 --> 08:32.120
Thanks. Gotta stay primed
for when the call comes in.

08:32.120 --> 08:35.079
Every weekend adds names
to the injury list, you know?

08:35.079 --> 08:37.473
I keep my toothbrush packed.You got the fans upset, man,

08:37.473 --> 08:39.736
saying the Wildcats
shouldn't have cut you.

08:39.736 --> 08:42.870
Yeah. People spread their love
for me. I know they did.

08:42.870 --> 08:44.698
No help. No help at all.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.700
Seems Twitter don't keep you
on a roster.

08:46.700 --> 08:49.398
Ah, I hear you.You follow football?

08:49.398 --> 08:51.748
Yeah. My dad and brother
made a point of it.

08:51.748 --> 08:54.272
Church and football
every Sunday -- not an option.

08:54.272 --> 08:56.318
But the pair of you didn't
come here to blah-blah

08:56.318 --> 08:57.928
about my career, did you?

08:57.928 --> 09:00.365
So just get to it, okay?
Before I cool down too much.

09:00.365 --> 09:04.239
Yeah, my bad. Uh, the night
Normandy Parker got killed --

09:04.239 --> 09:06.371
[ Sighs ]
Come on, man. For real?

09:06.371 --> 09:08.156
Hey, we just wanna see
where you were.

09:08.156 --> 09:10.245
Why? Billy James killed him.

09:10.245 --> 09:12.508
How do you know that?'Cause I know I didn't.

09:12.508 --> 09:14.249
Well, you point at a guy
in a locker room

09:14.249 --> 09:16.207
with a $2 million motive --Who said anything about a gun?

09:16.207 --> 09:17.600
Guy gets shot dead,

09:17.600 --> 09:19.602
people remember the first part,
you know?

09:19.602 --> 09:21.822
You're gonna ruin any chance
I got at a future.

09:21.822 --> 09:23.388
Only if you killed him, man.

09:23.388 --> 09:25.216
Look, just tell us
where you were,

09:25.216 --> 09:28.306
we'll let you get back
to your workout.[ Weights clank ]

09:28.306 --> 09:31.048
I was at home.
I saw it on the news.

09:31.048 --> 09:33.007
Popped a bottle of
the good stuff to celebrate.

09:33.007 --> 09:34.704
Couldn't have happened
to a better guy.

09:34.704 --> 09:36.619
An arrogant prick.

09:36.619 --> 09:38.752
Huh. All right, well, did you
share a glass with anybody else

09:38.752 --> 09:40.405
while the bottle was still open?

09:40.405 --> 09:41.929
Yeah, my girl.

09:41.929 --> 09:43.800
Your girl have a name?

09:43.800 --> 09:46.934
Yeah, she's got a name.
Willow.

09:46.934 --> 09:48.544
I'll tell her you're coming.

09:48.544 --> 09:52.069
Okay, all right.
Appreciate the cooperation, man.

09:52.069 --> 09:54.245
Thank you.Oh, just so we cover all
our bases,

09:54.245 --> 09:56.683
where were you when Billy James
got killed last Thursday?

09:56.683 --> 09:58.598
[ Chuckles ]

09:58.598 --> 10:01.601
Sure. I was principal for a day
at Jefferson High.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.038
You can see all the photos
of me online.

10:04.038 --> 10:06.649
Charity work is a part of
my anger management therapy.

10:06.649 --> 10:08.912
It really helps.

10:08.912 --> 10:10.740
All right, back to work.

10:14.004 --> 10:17.007
[ Mouth full ]
Guy owns a nationwide chain,

10:17.007 --> 10:19.314
prints money in his sleep,

10:19.314 --> 10:20.881
and he manages
to piss it all away.

10:20.881 --> 10:22.796
Mm.Great American tragedy.

10:22.796 --> 10:25.146
Yeah.
Riches to rags.

10:25.146 --> 10:28.584
And...Hello.

10:28.584 --> 10:30.325
Hello.
Oh.

10:30.325 --> 10:31.718
Mm.

10:34.546 --> 10:37.549
I like having you home.

10:37.549 --> 10:39.551
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:39.551 --> 10:41.858
[ Groans ]
Oh, come on.

10:41.858 --> 10:43.773
Okay, well, don't forget
where I was.

10:43.773 --> 10:45.906
I'm committing it
to memory.

10:45.906 --> 10:47.647
[ Chuckles ]

10:49.300 --> 10:50.780
May I help you?

10:50.780 --> 10:52.869
Um, is Mario home?

10:52.869 --> 10:55.567
Who are you?Just a friend.

10:55.567 --> 10:58.179
He left something in my car.

10:59.702 --> 11:01.922
Mario.What?

11:01.922 --> 11:03.967
Your friendis here.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.277
I'm sorry.

11:09.277 --> 11:11.540
Do I know you?[ Scoffs ]

11:11.540 --> 11:13.977
Mario Siletti?Yes.

11:13.977 --> 11:15.936
You've been served.Oh.

11:15.936 --> 11:17.459
Goddamnit.

11:17.459 --> 11:20.680
Oh...

11:20.680 --> 11:22.856
What? What is it?[ Door closes ]

11:22.856 --> 11:24.640
Well, I'm being sued.Yeah.

11:26.120 --> 11:28.122
For $15 million?

11:28.122 --> 11:29.819
Wait. What?!

11:29.819 --> 11:31.429
The woman's family.

11:31.429 --> 11:34.041
We haven't even started
the trial yet and now this?

11:34.041 --> 11:35.738
[ Whispers ] Oh, my God.

11:38.828 --> 11:41.483
What did you mean by
"your friend is here"?

11:41.483 --> 11:43.093
Hmm?

11:43.093 --> 11:47.619
No, I made a promise to you
to honor our marriage.

11:47.619 --> 11:50.927
How long before you actually
trust me again, hmm?

11:50.927 --> 11:53.625
What more can I do, Cass?

11:53.625 --> 11:55.323
I'm sorry.

11:55.323 --> 11:57.281
It's just that old scars --
they still hurt.

11:57.281 --> 11:58.979
You know,
this is a process.

12:02.243 --> 12:05.115
What are we gonna do?

12:09.206 --> 12:11.992
We'll handle it.

12:11.992 --> 12:13.384
Come here.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.779
[ Sighs ]

12:18.389 --> 12:21.610
[ Bell clanging ]

12:21.610 --> 12:24.178
SFPD.

12:24.178 --> 12:26.615
[ Sighs loudly ]

12:26.615 --> 12:28.095
Even if Willow answers,

12:28.095 --> 12:30.010
you know she's gonna
lie her ass off for him.

12:30.010 --> 12:32.099
See? Look at that.
You are a romantic.

12:32.099 --> 12:33.796
[ Chuckles ] I'm sure she
bounced the second he called.

12:33.796 --> 12:35.363
[ Knocking ]

12:35.363 --> 12:37.060
SFPD.[ Door closes ]

12:37.060 --> 12:38.409
What's going on?

12:38.409 --> 12:40.194
Uh, do you know
if Willow's home?

12:40.194 --> 12:41.978
Are you here about
her boyfriend?

12:41.978 --> 12:44.154
No, we're investigating
a homicide.

12:44.154 --> 12:46.504
Oh, my God.
Who did he kill?

12:46.504 --> 12:48.506
I was always afraid
it would be me.

12:48.506 --> 12:50.117
You know, you read about it,
the neighbor who

12:50.117 --> 12:51.509
calls the police and then
ends up needing them.

12:51.509 --> 12:53.207
You can't just listen
and do nothing,

12:53.207 --> 12:54.948
or you're part
of the problem, right?

12:54.948 --> 12:56.732
Listen to what?

12:56.732 --> 12:58.516
Oh, I won't come out my front
door if he's in the hall.

12:58.516 --> 13:00.692
I mean, if he hits her
and he loves her,

13:00.692 --> 13:02.477
what do you think
he'd do to me?

13:02.477 --> 13:05.045
I should move,
but I love my condo.

13:05.045 --> 13:08.048
9-1-1 is a joke.
Can't you guys help her?

13:08.048 --> 13:09.571
Uh, we'll follow up on that.

13:09.571 --> 13:11.181
When was the last time
you made a complaint?

13:13.793 --> 13:16.447
[ Cellphone buttons clicking ]May 17th.

13:19.102 --> 13:21.496
What?Koto: Okay, so let me
get this straight.

13:21.496 --> 13:23.150
Luke's alibi
for Normandy's murder

13:23.150 --> 13:25.152
is he was beating his girlfriend
at the time?

13:25.152 --> 13:27.371
Yeah. Dispatched confirmed
sending patrol.

13:27.371 --> 13:30.505
Uh, the reports say she was
bruised on her cheek

13:30.505 --> 13:31.941
and had a black eye.

13:31.941 --> 13:34.814
She claims
she ran into a door.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.554
Oh, doors are such a danger
to women, aren't they?

13:36.554 --> 13:39.035
Yeah.All the noise she said
came from TV.

13:39.035 --> 13:41.995
Other than that, after that,
it was peaceful in paradise.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.605
So the uniforms
turned around and left?

13:43.605 --> 13:45.650
Well, they gave him
a warning.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.000
[ Elevator bell dings ]I mean, this guy's still
a celebrity.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.392
The guy's
a violent asshole,

13:48.392 --> 13:49.741
but he didn't kill
either of our vics.

13:49.741 --> 13:53.354
Yeah. Oh.
Look what we got here.

13:53.354 --> 13:56.096
♪♪

13:56.096 --> 13:58.228
Oh.

13:58.228 --> 14:01.405
[ Chuckles ] Remind me
to never vacation in Reno.

14:01.405 --> 14:02.972
I heard that.

14:09.022 --> 14:11.067
So I-I took the company I built
from one sandwich shack

14:11.067 --> 14:13.461
to a food empire
and I bled it dry.

14:13.461 --> 14:15.550
I mean, there must've been
some sort of quarterly reports

14:15.550 --> 14:16.856
you had to file, right?

14:16.856 --> 14:18.509
Some sort
of checks and balances?

14:18.509 --> 14:20.685
You'd be surprised how easy
it is to take some money

14:20.685 --> 14:23.036
from Column "A" and put it
over to Column "B."

14:23.036 --> 14:24.646
How much are we talking?

14:24.646 --> 14:27.170
Well, it started out small
at first, you know?

14:27.170 --> 14:28.998
Phony consulting fee
here and there.

14:28.998 --> 14:30.565
But, man, once the ball
started rolling,

14:30.565 --> 14:32.872
I...I couldn't stop it.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.656
God knows how much
the company owes.

14:34.656 --> 14:37.267
Navarro:
Did Normandy know about this? Yes.

14:37.267 --> 14:40.401
Last season, I came to Norm
with a plan to fix a game.

14:40.401 --> 14:42.490
I hadn't funneled that much
money out of the company yet.

14:42.490 --> 14:44.405
I needed a sure thing
to bet my way out of trouble.

14:44.405 --> 14:47.756
Just -- Norm, he throws a few
bad passes, problem solved.

14:47.756 --> 14:49.366
So did he do it?

14:49.366 --> 14:51.064
No, Normandy was too proud
for something like that.

14:51.064 --> 14:53.675
He gave me a pretty nasty
tongue lashing, though.

14:53.675 --> 14:55.111
Told me to get my shit together.

14:55.111 --> 14:56.591
Why didn't Normandy just
sell his own shares?

14:56.591 --> 14:58.549
I mean, it's not like anyone
else knew the company

14:58.549 --> 15:02.162
was a fraud, right?That's --
that's not Norm's style.

15:02.162 --> 15:06.731
Look, guys like Norm -- they
don't think like you and me.

15:06.731 --> 15:08.908
Losing is not an option.

15:08.908 --> 15:12.041
So if Normandy didn't bail
you out, who did?Andy Chan.

15:12.041 --> 15:15.958
The Tongs became my bank.
Got to win a little bit,

15:15.958 --> 15:17.742
I put some money back
into the company

15:17.742 --> 15:21.007
so that nobody would notice,
and I'd lose and borrow more.

15:21.007 --> 15:22.225
Until the Tongs wanted
their money back.

15:22.225 --> 15:23.792
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

15:23.792 --> 15:25.533
Turns out it's easier
to defraud your own company

15:25.533 --> 15:27.796
than it is to put one over
on the Chinese mob.

15:27.796 --> 15:30.059
So you ran?Yeah, I needed time.

15:30.059 --> 15:32.540
I needed time to pay off
my debts.

15:32.540 --> 15:35.021
I needed time to start
a new life.

15:35.021 --> 15:37.153
Sometimes time is more valuable
than money.

15:37.153 --> 15:39.373
Yeah, you sure had enough time
to stop in Reno

15:39.373 --> 15:41.157
and play a few hands
of Blackjack.

15:41.157 --> 15:42.680
Not exactly
the best place to hide

15:42.680 --> 15:44.291
if you're trying to stay off
the grid, right?

15:44.291 --> 15:46.423
Hey, guys, that wasn't
my fault, okay?

15:46.423 --> 15:49.296
Gambler's GPS routed me through
Reno on my way to Canada.

15:49.296 --> 15:51.211
So you made it look like
the Tongs took you

15:51.211 --> 15:52.647
to give you more time?

15:52.647 --> 15:54.605
What -- what about
your girlfriend?

15:54.605 --> 15:56.433
I mean, she was scared half
to death. Did you consider her

15:56.433 --> 15:58.783
when you were planning all this?[ Scoffs ] She was in on it.

15:58.783 --> 16:02.091
[ Chuckles ]

16:02.091 --> 16:03.397
That's cold, man.

16:03.397 --> 16:06.008
Having your lady
take the heat for you?

16:06.008 --> 16:07.792
And lie to cops?

16:07.792 --> 16:10.230
Look, Amanda,
she -- she spent a semester

16:10.230 --> 16:12.493
at the Royal Academy
in London.

16:12.493 --> 16:14.625
Man, I tell you, that girl --
she can sell a line.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.888
Does Amanda know we have him?

16:16.888 --> 16:19.674
Yeah, I already told her.She thinks she's coming
to pick him up?

16:19.674 --> 16:21.676
It wasn't her fault. The only
thing she did wrong was

16:21.676 --> 16:23.765
trust that I-I would
do right by her. Yeah, you used her.

16:23.765 --> 16:26.376
Let's not get it twisted.You know what?
doesn't even matter.

16:26.376 --> 16:27.943
I'm a dead man, anyway.

16:27.943 --> 16:29.292
Soon as the Tongs find out
I'm alive,

16:29.292 --> 16:31.947
they're gonna find me,
chop me up,

16:31.947 --> 16:35.211
and feed me to the turtles
they sell down in Chinatown.

16:35.211 --> 16:37.387
Yeah, that sounds like a you
problem, not an us problem.

16:37.387 --> 16:39.911
No, it is an us problem
when I wind up dead.

16:39.911 --> 16:42.001
Come on, guys.
Why don't you just lock me up?

16:42.001 --> 16:43.437
I've already confessed
to fraud,

16:43.437 --> 16:45.004
countless S.E.C. violations.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.832
Please, send me to jail.

16:47.832 --> 16:50.400
[ Chair clatters ]You think a Tong lieutenant
like Chow

16:50.400 --> 16:52.185
can't get to you in jail?

16:52.185 --> 16:57.233
No. Not -- not jailjail.
I'm talking about good jail.

16:57.233 --> 16:59.061
Oh.Send me upstate

16:59.061 --> 17:01.803
where they have tennis courts
and put on talent shows.

17:01.803 --> 17:04.327
That's where I belong, with
other white collar criminals.

17:04.327 --> 17:06.895
Fine. Tell us why
you hired Billy James

17:06.895 --> 17:10.159
to kill Normandy Parker,
and I'll walk you down myself.

17:12.509 --> 17:14.076
What?

17:14.076 --> 17:15.991
W-what are you talking about?

17:15.991 --> 17:18.689
Are you kidding? That's why
you brought me back here?

17:18.689 --> 17:20.648
You think I killed Normandy?

17:20.648 --> 17:23.129
Molk: You had a key man policy
on Normandy's head.

17:23.129 --> 17:27.220
10 million bucks buys you
a lotof time.

17:27.220 --> 17:30.745
Hey, man...
[ Whispers ] I get it.

17:30.745 --> 17:32.225
[ Normal voice ]
You asked Normandy for a solid,

17:32.225 --> 17:35.619
and he spit in your face.

17:35.619 --> 17:39.884
It wouldn't have hurt him any
to throw one game.

17:39.884 --> 17:41.451
You tell us the truth,

17:41.451 --> 17:44.498
and we can try and make things
better for you.

17:44.498 --> 17:46.500
You got stuck,

17:46.500 --> 17:52.462
so you hired Billy James
to pop Normandy, didn't you?

17:52.462 --> 17:57.641
Look, me and Norm,
we're like family, okay?

17:57.641 --> 18:00.383
I know I've done some
horrible things,

18:00.383 --> 18:02.298
but I'm a good person.

18:02.298 --> 18:06.694
I would never, ever
do anything to Norm, ever.

18:06.694 --> 18:10.263
I would let the Tongs kill me
before I did that.

18:10.263 --> 18:11.916
You gotta believe me.

18:11.916 --> 18:13.918
All right, so he's
a degenerate gambler,

18:13.918 --> 18:16.225
probably steal from
the church collection plate,

18:16.225 --> 18:18.488
but I don't think
he's a killer.

18:18.488 --> 18:20.360
So he goes upstate
for embezzlement,

18:20.360 --> 18:22.753
and we're back to square one
with the Normandy case.

18:22.753 --> 18:25.104
Perfect.

18:29.282 --> 18:32.415
I haven't slept since
Sam's been missing.

18:32.415 --> 18:36.724
I kept running it in my head,
what could be happening to him,

18:36.724 --> 18:38.813
thinking I'd never see
him again.

18:38.813 --> 18:40.989
And I just wanted to die,
you know?

18:40.989 --> 18:43.644
Thank you, guys, so much
for bringing him home.

18:43.644 --> 18:45.428
Amanda?

18:45.428 --> 18:47.387
Oh, my God!

18:47.387 --> 18:49.128
Sammy.

18:49.128 --> 18:51.652
[ Laughs ]Oh, my God. Look at you.

18:51.652 --> 18:53.001
Oh.
What are you wearing?

18:53.001 --> 18:55.351
I don't care. You're here
and you're alive.

18:55.351 --> 18:58.311
And I was so scared --Amanda, you can --
you can drop the act, okay?

18:58.311 --> 18:59.921
I-I told them everything.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.665
Reno, Sam?

19:04.665 --> 19:06.362
I was all packed.

19:06.362 --> 19:07.624
[ Sighs ]

19:07.624 --> 19:09.452
Am I in trouble?

19:09.452 --> 19:11.019
Not if you leave now.

19:11.019 --> 19:13.978
Look, Aman-- just --I don't think so, Sam.

19:13.978 --> 19:17.852
S.E.C. is on its way.
Let's go.

19:17.852 --> 19:19.593
Hey.

19:19.593 --> 19:21.595
Shots were fired
in Alicia's house.

19:21.595 --> 19:25.468
SWAT's en route.
We should get going.

19:30.430 --> 19:34.477
[ Siren wails ]

19:34.477 --> 19:38.525
[ Indistinct shouting ]

19:38.525 --> 19:42.355
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

19:42.355 --> 19:46.359
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:46.359 --> 19:47.708
Barnes: Listen, the cops didn't
even give me time

19:47.708 --> 19:49.405
to open up the door.

19:49.405 --> 19:50.624
They just broke in.
They put assault weapons on me.

19:50.624 --> 19:52.016
They threw me down
on the ground.

19:52.016 --> 19:53.714
Nobody even told me why.Try to relax, sir.

19:53.714 --> 19:55.585
It's not that easy right now.An emergency call came in

19:55.585 --> 19:58.066
saying that there were
shots fired within the house.

19:58.066 --> 20:00.329
Where's your daughter?She's in rehab.

20:00.329 --> 20:02.636
Nothing happened here.
There were no shots fired.

20:02.636 --> 20:04.290
SWAT is still securing
the house.

20:04.290 --> 20:06.335
At this point, they're assuming
that it's a prank.

20:06.335 --> 20:08.250
They're doing it to celebrities
these days.

20:08.250 --> 20:10.644
It's called "swatting."That's sick.

20:10.644 --> 20:12.298
Are you staying in
the house right now, Mr. Barnes?

20:12.298 --> 20:13.995
Well, someone responsible's
gotta be here

20:13.995 --> 20:15.431
when she gets home, not
the crowd she's dealing with.

20:15.431 --> 20:17.781
Look at this. Look.

20:17.781 --> 20:20.915
Look at this.[ Bottles clink ]

20:20.915 --> 20:22.525
Look at this.Terry: Yeah.

20:22.525 --> 20:24.614
I'm trying to keep the house
safe for her, you know?

20:24.614 --> 20:26.573
Inspectors, we found this

20:26.573 --> 20:28.705
beneath the bed
in the master bedroom.

20:28.705 --> 20:31.230
It was loaded but it was not
discharged today.

20:31.230 --> 20:33.928
You found a loaded gun
in her bedroom?Thank you.

20:33.928 --> 20:36.583
Do you see
what I'm up against?

20:36.583 --> 20:39.325
Listen, you gotta get it
the hell out of here, okay?

20:39.325 --> 20:41.414
I can't have it around her.Yes, sir.

20:41.414 --> 20:46.027
Please, I'm just trying to keep
my daughter safe, guys.

20:47.942 --> 20:51.162
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:51.162 --> 20:53.121
[ Elevator bell dings ]Thank you.

20:53.121 --> 20:54.905
Hey.

20:54.905 --> 20:57.343
Hey.Hey, it occurred to me
I owe you half a dinner.

20:57.343 --> 20:59.432
'Cause you can't officially
call it a date

20:59.432 --> 21:01.260
if you only get
to the appetizers.

21:01.260 --> 21:04.654
Yeah, being a cop really
screws up your social life.

21:04.654 --> 21:06.526
Well, would you like to, uh,

21:06.526 --> 21:08.223
do the back-half
of dinner tonight?

21:08.223 --> 21:09.790
Yeah, sure.

21:09.790 --> 21:12.358
Cool. All right, um...[ Elevator bell dings ]

21:12.358 --> 21:13.794
7:00?
I'll pick you up at 7:00.

21:13.794 --> 21:15.665
7:00's good.
7:00's good.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.276
All right.

21:17.276 --> 21:19.539
All right. See you.Yeah, tonight.

21:22.281 --> 21:25.719
Hey.Hey, so the .22 that SWAT found
under Alicia's bed?

21:25.719 --> 21:27.721
Registered
to Andrew Lippman.

21:27.721 --> 21:30.593
Hmm. Lawyer/manager/bedmate.

21:30.593 --> 21:32.508
I heard that.Dude's full service, huh?

21:32.508 --> 21:36.599
[ Chuckles ] I goosed ballistics
to put a same day rush on it.

21:36.599 --> 21:38.253
For you.

21:38.253 --> 21:41.125
Oh. Thanks.
[ Clears throat ]

21:44.607 --> 21:45.913
[ Cup thuds ]

21:47.523 --> 21:49.351
$15 million?

21:49.351 --> 21:50.831
Who are they kidding?

21:50.831 --> 21:53.007
The woman worked
as a nurse, right?

21:53.007 --> 21:55.966
I mean, how much could she have
made in a year? What? $32K?

21:55.966 --> 21:57.533
Just take a deep breath.

21:57.533 --> 21:59.709
You have 30 days to respond.

21:59.709 --> 22:01.537
And I know the best
civil attorneys in town.

22:01.537 --> 22:03.844
[ Scoffs ] I can't afford
the best attorneys in town.

22:03.844 --> 22:05.498
I didn't say
the most expensive.

22:05.498 --> 22:07.978
All right, assuming we win
the criminal case,

22:07.978 --> 22:10.894
you should be able to settle
for 10 cents on the dollar.

22:10.894 --> 22:12.853
That's $1.5 million.

22:12.853 --> 22:15.638
That's under my liability limit.[ Envelope thuds ]

22:15.638 --> 22:18.075
[ Chuckles ]
I'm covered by insurance.

22:18.075 --> 22:19.381
I hate breaking bad news.

22:19.381 --> 22:21.122
No, I looked it up
already, Al.

22:21.122 --> 22:22.993
Even a real DUI doesn't change
the coverage.

22:22.993 --> 22:25.039
They still have to pay up
to the limit on my policy.

22:25.039 --> 22:26.649
I have zero exposure.

22:26.649 --> 22:30.044
Did you look up driving
with an expired license?

22:30.044 --> 22:32.046
Your insurance company
can deny the claim

22:32.046 --> 22:34.353
because you weren't legally
operating the vehicle

22:34.353 --> 22:36.006
at the time of the accident.

22:36.006 --> 22:38.661
Are you sure?I do this for a living.

22:41.447 --> 22:43.623
How could you not renew
your driver's license

22:43.623 --> 22:45.451
for a whole year?

22:45.451 --> 22:48.323
We can't even make the argument
that it was slightly expired.

22:48.323 --> 22:50.456
I was busy.All right, well,

22:50.456 --> 22:51.848
you still have equity
in your house, though, right?

22:51.848 --> 22:54.024
I'm not at fault. My house?

22:54.024 --> 22:56.375
Money is the least of your
problems if you're in jail.

22:56.375 --> 22:59.334
We need to focus on our case.
We've received discovery.

22:59.334 --> 23:01.554
Already?Well, you wanted to
fast-track the trial,

23:01.554 --> 23:03.338
and the State is
making it happen for you.

23:03.338 --> 23:05.253
Not a favor,
I'll tell you again.

23:05.253 --> 23:07.690
Delays are a defense attorney's
best friend.

23:07.690 --> 23:09.039
You're still thinking like
a prosecutor.

23:09.039 --> 23:10.780
'Cause the sooner
this is over,

23:10.780 --> 23:13.043
the sooner I can get back
to the right side of the aisle.

23:13.043 --> 23:15.872
I never would have produced
discovery that fast.

23:15.872 --> 23:18.048
[ Scoffs ] You know, I used to
give old contact info

23:18.048 --> 23:20.311
for the witnesses just to make
the defense work harder.

23:20.311 --> 23:22.009
Yeah, nice.
Very professional.

23:22.009 --> 23:23.750
Oh, please. You know how much
the defense withholds.

23:23.750 --> 23:25.969
Don't get all prissy on me.

23:25.969 --> 23:27.928
There's an eyewitness
to the accident.

23:27.928 --> 23:31.061
No, there wasn't.Yeah, she's on
the State's list.

23:31.061 --> 23:32.759
Her name is Skylar Jennings.

23:32.759 --> 23:36.197
Let me see her statement.Well, it's a partial.

23:36.197 --> 23:38.721
She says she was at
or near the scene.

23:38.721 --> 23:41.420
She observed the events
in their entirety.

23:41.420 --> 23:43.422
She declined to complete
her statement

23:43.422 --> 23:45.902
pending further discussions
with the DA's office.

23:45.902 --> 23:48.557
State's back pocket witness.Yeah, I ran her record.

23:48.557 --> 23:51.778
Repeated arrests for narcotics,
vandalism, criminal trespassing.

23:51.778 --> 23:54.215
And pending charges.Exactly.

23:54.215 --> 23:55.869
She's a junkie snitch.
She's looking to cut a deal.

23:55.869 --> 23:57.392
[ Files thud ]She can't hurt us.

23:57.392 --> 23:58.872
I am more worried about
your wife.

23:58.872 --> 24:00.526
I thought we agreed
about this.

24:00.526 --> 24:02.484
If the State gets her to admit
that you two were having

24:02.484 --> 24:04.094
an argument at the time
of the accident,

24:04.094 --> 24:05.922
it supports negligence.

24:05.922 --> 24:08.185
You were drunk anddistracted.
Why would you risk that?

24:08.185 --> 24:10.187
There is no risk.

24:10.187 --> 24:13.582
Okay? Cassie will testify
that I was sober in the car.

24:13.582 --> 24:15.105
And she will also establish

24:15.105 --> 24:17.325
that the victim
was impossible to see.

24:17.325 --> 24:19.849
I had no way
to stop in time.

24:19.849 --> 24:23.287
The sole cause of this accident
is the victim's own negligence.

24:24.941 --> 24:29.293
You'll find a respectful way
to put that.

24:32.819 --> 24:34.951
I took your advice, Al.

24:34.951 --> 24:36.344
Cassie and I are
getting along

24:36.344 --> 24:38.781
better than we have
in a long time.

24:38.781 --> 24:41.436
It's a terrible way
to save your marriage, but...

24:43.133 --> 24:45.745
She won't do anything
to hurt us.

24:45.745 --> 24:47.050
[ Mouths word ]

24:48.356 --> 24:50.358
Okay.[ Tapping ]

24:50.358 --> 24:53.883
Thank you very much.What?

24:53.883 --> 24:56.625
Ballistics fingerprinting shows
that Andrew Lippman's gun

24:56.625 --> 24:59.367
is the exact match to the gun
that killed Normandy Parker.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.978
We've got our murder weapon.Let's go get this guy.

25:01.978 --> 25:04.154
♪♪

25:10.160 --> 25:11.814
Yes, I bought Alicia the gun
for protection from stalkers

25:11.814 --> 25:14.208
in case any of them got past
her security.

25:14.208 --> 25:16.906
Look, I have no idea
how Billy got a hold of it.

25:16.906 --> 25:18.995
Or how the murder weapon
ended up in her house?

25:18.995 --> 25:20.693
Under her bed?

25:20.693 --> 25:23.173
You're not seriously trying
to lay Normandy's murder

25:23.173 --> 25:25.393
on my client, are you?

25:25.393 --> 25:29.528
Or is this to make the new DA
famous worldwide?

25:29.528 --> 25:31.138
Look, she is too fragile

25:31.138 --> 25:33.793
to go through
some ridiculous shitstorm.

25:33.793 --> 25:36.056
Come on. Don't do this.
This makes no sense.

25:36.056 --> 25:37.840
We're not looking at her,
though.

25:37.840 --> 25:39.407
We're looking at you.

25:39.407 --> 25:42.497
What?

25:42.497 --> 25:44.978
Me? [ Chuckles ]

25:44.978 --> 25:47.154
[ Laughs ]

25:47.154 --> 25:48.808
Uh, okay. Okay, look.

25:48.808 --> 25:52.376
I-I-I understand that you are
under maxi pressure

25:52.376 --> 25:54.030
to identify somebody.

25:54.030 --> 25:56.380
Look, anybody
resembling a suspect

25:56.380 --> 25:58.208
in a double murder here.

25:58.208 --> 25:59.775
But -- but me?[ Clears throat ]

25:59.775 --> 26:02.212
Well, just look at it
from our perspective.

26:02.212 --> 26:04.301
You were with Alicia way before
Normandy.

26:04.301 --> 26:06.303
He pushed you out.
You know, he took over.

26:06.303 --> 26:07.827
She didn't need you anymore.

26:07.827 --> 26:11.178
Yeah, I was pissed. You bet.
I said some things.

26:11.178 --> 26:12.919
But not threats.

26:12.919 --> 26:15.182
Not death threats.

26:15.182 --> 26:18.315
And then I moved on because
business is the priority.

26:18.315 --> 26:20.927
And you know what? Normandy, he
was actually good for business.

26:20.927 --> 26:23.059
He made Alicia stable
ways I never could.

26:23.059 --> 26:24.800
I was grateful to him
eventually.

26:24.800 --> 26:26.715
You and Billy were tight,
though, right?

26:26.715 --> 26:29.283
No. I was not tightwith...

26:29.283 --> 26:31.328
We were in the same rooms
at the same times.

26:31.328 --> 26:34.157
He was with Normandy. I was with
Alicia. They were together.

26:34.157 --> 26:36.551
Until the two of them
got rid of the two of you,

26:36.551 --> 26:39.510
and you convinced Billy to solve
your little mutual problem.

26:39.510 --> 26:42.731
Arrest me and Mirandize me

26:42.731 --> 26:45.342
or let me walk out
that door.

26:45.342 --> 26:47.127
Did Billy try to squeeze you
for more money,

26:47.127 --> 26:48.824
but you knew it was never
gonna be over

26:48.824 --> 26:50.870
while he was still breathing?
Is that what happened?

26:50.870 --> 26:56.266
I had nothing to do
with killing anyone.

26:56.266 --> 26:59.530
When Billy was shot, I was
taking my regular spin class

26:59.530 --> 27:02.577
in Bernal Heights
at Spin Spirit Studio.

27:02.577 --> 27:04.448
I'm covered.

27:04.448 --> 27:06.320
You check it out.

27:06.320 --> 27:09.192
And now...may I leave?

